<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-06T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="303" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/781: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port au
                                        Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-06T12:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 6,
                                        1919, 12 noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                    January 8, 10.45 p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>From Ruan:</p>
                        <p>“In event agreement as to settlement accounts due Banque Nationale de la
                            République de Haiti, as suggested in Department December 4, 6 p.m., is
                            effected will bank proceed immediately with monetary reform in
                            accordance with plan presented to Santallier in March 1918, a copy of
                            which was transmitted Department with my letter to Mr. Stabler, March
                            16th, 1918?”</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>